==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: aneurysm
<hw>an"eu*rysm</hw></mhw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n"⟦usl⟧*r⟦icr⟧z'm)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'aney`rysma</grk>, <grk>'aneyrysmo`s</grk>, a widening, an opening;
<grk>'ana`</grk> up + <grk>e'yry`s</grk> wide.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A soft, usually pulsating, sac, containing blood or blood clot,
arising from the abnormal dilation of the walls of an artery, vein or
heart. The more common spelling is <ex>aneurysm</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>aneurismal</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Aneurysmal</ent>⟦br⟧
